The key insight to solve this problem is to recognize that the area of the overlapping region can be calculated by multiplying the width and height of the overlapping rectangle. The width of the overlapping region is the width of the smaller sheet of paper ($8.5$ inches), and the height of the overlapping region is the height of the larger sheet of paper ($8$ inches).
